#: ../../../advanced/cluster-programming.md:96
msgid "Distributed shared memory (DSMEM)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/cluster-programming.md:98
msgid ""
"The core feature of clusters is cross-block shared memory access. There are "
"two ways to read a remote block's shared memory:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/cluster-programming.md:101
msgid "Method 1: map_shared_rank (pointer remapping)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/cluster-programming.md:103
msgid ""
"`map_shared_rank` takes a local shared memory pointer and returns a pointer "
"to the same offset in another block's shared memory:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/cluster-programming.md:106
msgid ""
"use cuda_device::{cluster, SharedArray, thread};\n"
"\n"
"static mut DATA: SharedArray<u32, 256> = SharedArray::UNINIT;\n"
"\n"
"#[kernel]\n"
"#[cluster_launch(4, 1, 1)]\n"
"pub fn halo_exchange(/* ... */) {\n"
"    let tid = thread::threadIdx_x() as usize;\n"
"    let rank = cluster::block_rank();\n"
"\n"
"    // Each block writes its own shared memory\n"
"    unsafe { DATA[tid] = compute_value(rank, tid); }\n"
"\n"
"    thread::sync_threads();    // local barrier first\n"
"    cluster::cluster_sync();   // then cluster-wide barrier\n"
"\n"
"    // Read from the next block's shared memory\n"
"    let neighbor = (rank + 1) % cluster::cluster_size();\n"
"    let remote_ptr = unsafe {\n"
"        cluster::map_shared_rank(DATA.as_ptr().add(tid), neighbor)\n"
"    };\n"
"    let neighbor_val = unsafe { *remote_ptr };\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/cluster-programming.md:132
msgid "Method 2: dsmem_read_u32 (preferred)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/cluster-programming.md:134
msgid ""
"`dsmem_read_u32` is the preferred way to read remote shared memory. It "
"compiles to the `ld.shared::cluster` PTX instruction, which the hardware "
"handles more efficiently than a generic load through a remapped pointer:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/cluster-programming.md:138
msgid ""
"let neighbor_val = unsafe {\n"
"    cluster::dsmem_read_u32(\n"
"        DATA.as_ptr() as *const u32,\n"
"        neighbor,  // target rank\n"
"    )\n"
"};\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/cluster-programming.md:147
msgid ""
"The difference is subtle but matters for performance: `map_shared_rank` "
"produces a pointer that goes through the generic load path, while "
"`dsmem_read_u32` uses a dedicated instruction that the hardware can "
"optimize. Use `dsmem_read_u32` for `u32`-sized reads; for larger types, "
"`map_shared_rank` with the appropriate pointer type works."
msgstr ""

